description_of_request:
Requesting records related to the creation, initial publishing, and subsequent amendment of the website of the Chicago Monuments Project of which your department is a sponsor. Specifically, I am requesting documents held by your department including but not limited to:
The initial drafts of the descriptions to be used to describe each of the 41 monument identified for further discussion on the website;
Comments and/or amendments by city staff or others to those initial drafts;
The process for approval and the city authorities who approved the website content prior to publication/release;
The original description of each monument on the list of monuments under review when the Chicago Monuments Project when the website was first published.
A record of all change an amendments to those descriptions up to the date of this request including a record of approvals; 
Any correspondence, discussions, or documentation concerning amendments to the either those descriptions or the design or wording or the website in general.

In accordance with the Illinois Freedom of Information Act, National Corporate Research, Ltd. hereby requests copies of the following public records: All correspondence between any employee of the Department of Cultural Affairs and Special Events and Chris Kennedy (a.k.a. Christopher Kennedy), between October 1, 2000 and present day. All correspondence between any employee of the Department of Cultural Affairs and Special Events and Ike Saunders, between July 1, 2009 and present day. Records of payments, reimbursements, per diems, or any other monetary awards given to Chris Kennedy (a.k.a. Christopher Kennedy) between January 1, 1993 and present day;

Records of expenses submitted by Chris Kennedy (a.k.a. Christopher Kennedy) between January 1, 1993 and present day;

Records of all direct payments made by the Department of Cultural Affairs and Special Events and/or the Chicago Convention and Tourism Bureau for expenses incurred by Chris Kennedy (a.k.a. Christopher Kennedy) between January 1, 1993 and present day;

Records of any travel or lodging undertaken by Chris Kennedy (a.k.a. Christopher Kennedy) between January 1, 1993 and present day. This includes final folios for all hotel stays that include all transactions – including incidentals – incurred during the stay, and detailed travel reservations that include seat numbers, class of travel and any added amenities (such as extra leg room, access to travel lounges, etc.); 

Any documents relating to the appointment of Chris Kennedy to the Chicago Convention and Tourism Bureau and his chairmanship (which occurred between March 1, 1997 and January 1, 2000), including but not limited to: cover letters, letters of recommendation, curriculum vitae(s), questionnaires, applications, interview notes, and similar material;

Any audits or reviews of the Chicago Convention and Tourism Bureau between March 1, 1997 and January 1, 2000.

Requesting documents for Oktoberfest that took place on Sept. 25, 2016, Oct. 4, 2015 & Sept. 21, 2014 and Rogers Pork that took place on Aug. 27, 2016, Aug. 29, 2015 & Aug. 23, 2014, both event were located in the block of 1500 W. Jarvis Ave., Chicago. IL 60626 (between 1500-1508 W Jarvis Ave.), including
(1) Police District Commander Review Letter;
(2) Alderman Joseph Moore Approval /or objection letter;
(3) State of Illinois Special Event/Special Use Liquor License
(4) Proof of payment for event application, payable to City of Chicago;
(5) Terms and Conditions/Signature of Organizer page
